  "commentary": "With SPX at 6762.28 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6750 (-52.3B) and max positive gamma at 6800 (+24.4B), dealers are likely buying this dip given the proximity to the massive amplifying wall at 6750. The breakout regime with -168.4B total GEX means any move will be amplified by dealer hedging - if we break below 6750, expect accelerated selling as dealers chase the move lower, while a push toward 6800 will trigger dealer selling pressure. Watch 6750 as the critical inflection point, with the cluster of negative gamma walls from 6750-6770 creating a minefield of amplifying hedging flows.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings with big moves in either direction getting amplified by dealer hedging.",
